A cleric has charged all Christians to embark on fervent prayers in 2020 in order to avert disharmony among religious groups. The founder of Joyous Miracle Gospel Church and Ministry, Ogbomoso, Oyo State, Apostle Johnson Afolabi, said this during the prophecy for 2020 and interdenominational service recently. Apostle Afolabi told TribuneChurch that some elements would like to use their positions to sow seeds of discord among religious organisations in the land which could cause crises. VIDEO: Pandemonium as pipeline explodes in Lagos Supreme Court to deliver judgment in Kano, Sokoto guber… Northern Youth Forum appoints Bowen VC as ‘Garkuwan… PDP condemns APC’s defense of Imo guber judgement “We need to call on God all the time so that dark days will not happen again in Nigeria. God will reveal and shame those that want to cause bloodshed in the country and they would meet their Waterloo ithis year. “Lawmakers should not be lawbreakers, the love of materialism should not overshadow divine justice and righteousness from God,” he said. He, however, advised clerics to stop preaching prosperity and luxury, but to seek first the kingdom of God and its righteousness in their lives. Apostle Afolabi disclosed that 2020 will bring God’s blessings to Nigeria despite challenges facing the country. STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO  WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS FREE